--- Comment #2 from Alex Deucher <alexdeucher@gmail.com> ---
This is the expected behavior for multiple monitors on Linux.  mclk switchi=
ng
must happen in the monitors' blanking period.  Since they likely don't alig=
n,
especially if the monitors have different timing, we have to use a fixed mc=
lk.=20
The DC modesetting code can lock the timing of multiple monitors if they are
using the exact same timing so that the blanking periods align, but I don't
think the Linux power management code takes this into account at the moment.

--=20
